COMPLEX VERTEBRAL MALFORMATION, BOVINE - DENMARK: RFI
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 4 Jan 2001 05:38:50 -0800 (PST)
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

Danish researchers are puzzled by what is believed to be a new disease in
dairy cows, tentatively known as complex vertebral malformation. The
disease is characterized by malformations in aborted fetuses and in
prematurely born, stillborn and neonatal Holstein calves. The researchers
believe that the defect is inherited as a simple recessive trait, but U.S.
researchers want more information.
