[Would any members with information please share it with us. While such
conditions may well be genetic, and thus inappropriate for ProMED-mail
posting, in my experience there are a number of teratogenic infections of
livestock that might be involved in such a condition. Additionally, we can
always be surprised by a new one. Too often I have read genetic
explanations for what have later turned out to be fetal infections. I would
rather make a fool of myself than miss a new infectious disease. - Mod.MHJ]
